div.p:
Do you see how it is not the pain of the body which has been quieted and reduced to silence, but the pain of the soul which has been chastened by rebuke and reduced to silence? And so at the end of the Niptra1 he rebukes others as well, and that in his last moments:


It befits not to complain of adverse fortune or bemoan;

This man's duty is: on women's nature weeping was bestowed.
